            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJoshua%20rebuked%20the%20seven%20tribes%20who%20had%20not%20yet%20asserted%20their%20victory%20over%20the%20Canaanites.%20Why%3F%20Like%20many%20of%20us%2C%20they%20were%20waiting%20for%20God%2C%20while%20in%20reality%20God%20was%20waiting%20for%20them!%20Joshua's%20rebuke%20to%20the%20Israelites%20was%20that%20though%20God%20had%20already%20given%20them%20the%20land%2C%20they%20refused%20to%20pay%20the%20price%20to%20possess%20it.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20lazy%20steward%20of%20Luke%2019%3A20%20demonstrated%20no%20initiative%20to%20become%20involved%20in%20the%20risky%2C%20dangerous%20world%20of%20investment.%20He%20simply%20took%20the%20money%20his%20master%20had%20given%20him%20and%20hid%20it%20away.%20Though%20he%20blamed%20his%20master%20for%20his%20lack%20of%20effort%2C%20the%20real%20fault%20lay%20with%20him.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20has%20given%20you%20certain%20talents%20and%20gifts%2C%20but%20He%20will%20never%20force%20you%20to%20use%20them.%20Yes%2C%20it%20will%20cost%20you%20something%20to%20use%20your%20talents%2C%20and%20you%20may%20even%20fail%20once%20or%20twice.%20You%20will%20have%20to%20practice%2C%20sacrifice%2C%20and%20learn%2C%20but%20you%20can%20do%20all%20things%20through%20Christ%20who%20strengthens%20you%20(Philippians%204%3A13).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EStep%20out%20of%20the%20boat%20and%20onto%20the%20water%20as%20Peter%20did.%20Your%20eternal%20reward%20depends%20upon%20your%20assertiveness%2C%20so%20stop%20being%20passive%20and%20go%20take%20a%20few%20cities!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Joshua.16:1-18:28",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJoshua%2016%3A1-18%3A28%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_1%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJoshua%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Ephraim%20and%20West%20Manasseh%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20allotment%20for%20the%20descendants%20of%20Joseph%20extended%20from%20the%20Jordan%20River%20near%20Jericho%2C%20east%20of%20the%20springs%20of%20Jericho%2C%20through%20the%20wilderness%20and%20into%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Bethel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_2%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20Bethel%20(that%20is%2C%20Luz)%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E16%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20(also%20see%2018%3A13)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EFrom%20Bethel%20to%20Luz.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20it%20ran%20over%20to%20Ataroth%20in%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Arkites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_3%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20it%20descended%20westward%20to%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Japhletites%20as%20far%20as%20Lower%20Beth-horon%2C%20then%20to%20Gezer%20and%20over%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E16%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2016%3A6%2C%208.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_4%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20was%20the%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20families%20of%20Joseph%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons%2C%20Manasseh%20and%20Ephraim.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_5%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20Ephraim%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20following%20territory%20was%20given%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3EThe%20boundary%20of%20their%20homeland%20began%20at%20Ataroth-addar%20in%20the%20east.%20From%20there%20it%20ran%20to%20Upper%20Beth-horon%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_6%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20on%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%20From%20Micmethath%20on%20the%20north%2C%20the%20boundary%20curved%20eastward%20past%20Taanath-shiloh%20to%20the%20east%20of%20Janoah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_7%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20Janoah%20it%20turned%20southward%20to%20Ataroth%20and%20Naarah%2C%20touched%20Jericho%2C%20and%20ended%20at%20the%20Jordan%20River.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_8%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20Tappuah%20the%20boundary%20extended%20westward%2C%20following%20the%20Kanah%20Ravine%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%20This%20is%20the%20homeland%20allocated%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_9%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20some%20towns%20with%20their%20surrounding%20villages%20in%20the%20territory%20allocated%20to%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20were%20set%20aside%20for%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_16_10%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20did%20not%20drive%20the%20Canaanites%20out%20of%20Gezer%2C%20however%2C%20so%20the%20people%20of%20Gezer%20live%20as%20slaves%20among%20the%20people%20of%20Ephraim%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_1%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJoshua%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20West%20Manasseh%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20next%20allotment%20of%20land%20was%20given%20to%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh%2C%20the%20descendants%20of%20Joseph%26%23x2019%3Bs%20older%20son.%20Makir%2C%20the%20firstborn%20son%20of%20Manasseh%2C%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Gilead.%20Because%20his%20descendants%20were%20experienced%20soldiers%2C%20the%20regions%20of%20Gilead%20and%20Bashan%20on%20the%20east%20side%20of%20the%20Jordan%20had%20already%20been%20given%20to%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_2%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20allotment%20on%20the%20west%20side%20of%20the%20Jordan%20was%20for%20the%20remaining%20families%20within%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Manasseh%3A%20Abiezer%2C%20Helek%2C%20Asriel%2C%20Shechem%2C%20Hepher%2C%20and%20Shemida.%20These%20clans%20represent%20the%20male%20descendants%20of%20Manasseh%20son%20of%20Joseph.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_3%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20Zelophehad%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20Hepher%20son%20of%20Gilead%2C%20son%20of%20Makir%2C%20son%20of%20Manasseh%2C%20had%20no%20sons.%20He%20had%20only%20daughters%2C%20whose%20names%20were%20Mahlah%2C%20Noah%2C%20Hoglah%2C%20Milcah%2C%20and%20Tirzah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_4%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20women%20came%20to%20Eleazar%20the%20priest%2C%20Joshua%20son%20of%20Nun%2C%20and%20the%20Israelite%20leaders%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20commanded%20Moses%20to%20give%20us%20a%20grant%20of%20land%20along%20with%20the%20men%20of%20our%20tribe.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ESo%20Joshua%20gave%20them%20a%20grant%20of%20land%20along%20with%20their%20uncles%2C%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20commanded.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_5%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Manasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20total%20allocation%20came%20to%20ten%20parcels%20of%20land%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Gilead%20and%20Bashan%20across%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_6%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Ebecause%20the%20female%20descendants%20of%20Manasseh%20received%20a%20grant%20of%20land%20along%20with%20the%20male%20descendants.%20(The%20land%20of%20Gilead%20was%20given%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20male%20descendants%20of%20Manasseh.)%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_7%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20boundary%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20extended%20from%20the%20border%20of%20Asher%20to%20Micmethath%2C%20near%20Shechem.%20Then%20the%20boundary%20went%20south%20from%20Micmethath%20to%20the%20settlement%20near%20the%20spring%20of%20Tappuah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_8%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20land%20surrounding%20Tappuah%20belonged%20to%20Manasseh%2C%20but%20the%20town%20of%20Tappuah%20itself%2C%20on%20the%20border%20of%20Manasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory%2C%20belonged%20to%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_9%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20spring%20of%20Tappuah%2C%20the%20boundary%20of%20Manasseh%20followed%20the%20Kanah%20Ravine%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2017%3A10.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Several%20towns%20south%20of%20the%20ravine%20were%20inside%20Manasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory%2C%20but%20they%20actually%20belonged%20to%20the%20tribe%20of%20Ephraim.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_10%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20general%2C%20however%2C%20the%20land%20south%20of%20the%20ravine%20belonged%20to%20Ephraim%2C%20and%20the%20land%20north%20of%20the%20ravine%20belonged%20to%20Manasseh.%20Manasseh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20boundary%20ran%20along%20the%20northern%20side%20of%20the%20ravine%20and%20ended%20at%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%20North%20of%20Manasseh%20was%20the%20territory%20of%20Asher%2C%20and%20to%20the%20east%20was%20the%20territory%20of%20Issachar.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_11%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20following%20towns%20within%20the%20territory%20of%20Issachar%20and%20Asher%2C%20however%2C%20were%20given%20to%20Manasseh%3A%20Beth-shan%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A11a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EBeth-shean%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Beth-shan%3B%20also%20in%2017%3A16.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Ibleam%2C%20Dor%20(that%20is%2C%20Naphoth-dor)%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A11b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20here%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Endor%2C%20Taanach%2C%20and%20Megiddo%2C%20each%20with%20their%20surrounding%20settlements.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_12%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20descendants%20of%20Manasseh%20were%20unable%20to%20occupy%20these%20towns%20because%20the%20Canaanites%20were%20determined%20to%20stay%20in%20that%20region.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_13%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3ELater%2C%20however%2C%20when%20the%20Israelites%20became%20strong%20enough%2C%20they%20forced%20the%20Canaanites%20to%20work%20as%20slaves.%20But%20they%20did%20not%20drive%20them%20out%20of%20the%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_14%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20descendants%20of%20Joseph%20came%20to%20Joshua%20and%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20have%20you%20given%20us%20only%20one%20portion%20of%20land%20as%20our%20homeland%20when%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20blessed%20us%20with%20so%20many%20people%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_15%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EJoshua%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIf%20there%20are%20so%20many%20of%20you%2C%20and%20if%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim%20is%20not%20large%20enough%20for%20you%2C%20clear%20out%20land%20for%20yourselves%20in%20the%20forest%20where%20the%20Perizzites%20and%20Rephaites%20live.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_16%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20descendants%20of%20Joseph%20responded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIt%26%23x2019%3Bs%20true%20that%20the%20hill%20country%20is%20not%20large%20enough%20for%20us.%20But%20all%20the%20Canaanites%20in%20the%20lowlands%20have%20iron%20chariots%2C%20both%20those%20in%20Beth-shan%20and%20its%20surrounding%20settlements%20and%20those%20in%20the%20valley%20of%20Jezreel.%20They%20are%20too%20strong%20for%20us.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_17%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Joshua%20said%20to%20the%20tribes%20of%20Ephraim%20and%20Manasseh%2C%20the%20descendants%20of%20Joseph%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BSince%20you%20are%20so%20large%20and%20strong%2C%20you%20will%20be%20given%20more%20than%20one%20portion.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_17_18%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20forests%20of%20the%20hill%20country%20will%20be%20yours%20as%20well.%20Clear%20as%20much%20of%20the%20land%20as%20you%20wish%2C%20and%20take%20possession%20of%20its%20farthest%20corners.%20And%20you%20will%20drive%20out%20the%20Canaanites%20from%20the%20valleys%2C%20too%2C%20even%20though%20they%20are%20strong%20and%20have%20iron%20chariots.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_1%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJoshua%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Allotments%20of%20the%20Remaining%20Land%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20that%20the%20land%20was%20under%20Israelite%20control%2C%20the%20entire%20community%20of%20Israel%20gathered%20at%20Shiloh%20and%20set%20up%20the%20Tabernacle.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ETent%20of%20Meeting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_2%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20there%20remained%20seven%20tribes%20who%20had%20not%20yet%20been%20allotted%20their%20grants%20of%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_3%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Joshua%20asked%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHow%20long%20are%20you%20going%20to%20wait%20before%20taking%20possession%20of%20the%20remaining%20land%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20your%20ancestors%2C%20has%20given%20to%20you%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_4%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESelect%20three%20men%20from%20each%20tribe%2C%20and%20I%20will%20send%20them%20out%20to%20explore%20the%20land%20and%20map%20it%20out.%20They%20will%20then%20return%20to%20me%20with%20a%20written%20report%20of%20their%20proposed%20divisions%20of%20their%20new%20homeland.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_5%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ELet%20them%20divide%20the%20land%20into%20seven%20sections%2C%20excluding%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory%20in%20the%20south%20and%20Joseph%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory%20in%20the%20north.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_6%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20when%20you%20record%20the%20seven%20divisions%20of%20the%20land%20and%20bring%20them%20to%20me%2C%20I%20will%20cast%20sacred%20lots%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%20to%20assign%20land%20to%20each%20tribe.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_18_7%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20Levites%2C%20however%2C%20will%20not%20receive%20any%20allotment%20of%20land.%20Their%20role%20as%20priests%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20their%20allotment.%20And%20the%20tribes%20of%20Gad%2C%20Reuben%2C%20and%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20won%26%23x2019%3Bt%20receive%20any%20more%20land%2C%20for%20they%20have%20already%20received%20their%20grant%20of%20land%2C%20which%20Moses%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20gave%20them%20on%20the%20east%20s